climate[edit] lakshadweep islands gulmarg in india, it rains only during a specific time of the year. the season as well as the phenomenon that causes it is called the monsoon. there are two of them, the southwest and the northeast, both named after the directions the winds come from. the southwest monsoon is the more important one, as it causes rains over most parts of the country, and is the crucial variable that decides how the crops will do. it lasts from june to september. the southwest monsoon hits the west coast the most, as crossing the western ghats and 